#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/security/shb-limits.xml:141
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Linux kernel will track the quota usage as the system works. If for any\n"
"reason the quota files become corrupt or you think the data is wrong, you will\n"
"need to bring the system in single-user mode (or at least ensure that the file\n"
"systems are not being actively written to) and then call <c>quotacheck\n"
"-avugm</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><body><p>
#: en/security/shb-limits.xml:149
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After rebooting the machine, it is time to setup the quotas for users and\n"
"groups. <c>edquota -u kn</c> will start the editor defined in $EDITOR (default\n"
"is nano) and let you edit the quotas of the user kn. <c>edquota -g</c> will do\n"
"the same thing for groups.\n"
msgstr ""
"マシンを再起動した後、ユーザとグループのquotaが設定します。\n"
"<c>edquota -u kn</c>を実行すると、$EDITORに定義されたエディタが起動し (デフォルトはnano)、ユーザknに対するquotaの設定を行います。\n"
"<c>edquota -g</c>を実行すればグループに対して同様の事を行います。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><body><pre>
#: en/security/shb-limits.xml:155
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
